drives = read.csv("https://remiller1450.github.io/data/drives.csv")
library(ggplot2)
library(tidyr)
library(dplyr)
## 
## Attaching package: 'dplyr'
## The following objects are masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter, lag
## The following objects are masked from 'package:base':
## 
##     intersect, setdiff, setequal, union

Visualization 1

drives1 <- drives %>%
  na.omit() %>%
  group_by(Subject, Drive) %>%
  mutate(total_depts = sum(LaneDeparts_Left) + sum(LaneDeparts_Right)) %>%
  filter(EventNum == "304")
drives %>% 
  count(EventNum)
##   EventNum  n
## 1      304 92
## 2      308 57
## 3      311 92
ggplot(drives1, aes(total_depts, fill = Drive, color = Drive)) +
  geom_histogram(bins=10, alpha = 0.5) + theme_minimal() +
  facet_wrap(~Drive) +
  labs(x = "Total Number of Departures", y = "Frequency") +
  scale_fill_manual(values = c(RT1 = "red", RT2 = "lightgreen", RT3 = "cyan", RT4 = "orange")) +
  scale_color_manual(values = c(RT1 = "red", RT2 = "lightgreen", RT3 = "cyan", RT4 = "orange")) +
  theme(strip.background = element_rect(color = "white", fill="white"))

# Visualization 2
target <- read.csv("https://collinn.github.io/teaching/2023/data/target.csv")
cohort <- read.csv("https://collinn.github.io/teaching/2023/data/cohort.csv")

tc <- left_join(x = target, y = cohort, by = c("subjectID", "time"))
                
tclong <- pivot_longer(tc,
                       cols = !c(subjectID, time),
                       names_to = "Type",
                       values_to = "Probability")
tcsep <- separate(tclong,
                  col = Type,
                  into = c("Sound", "Type"),
                  sep = "\\.")

ggplot(tcsep, aes(time, Probability)) +
  geom_line(aes(group = subjectID, color = factor(subjectID))) + 
  geom_smooth(color = "Black") +
  facet_grid(Sound~Type) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position="none")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula = 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'

# Extra
target2 <- read.csv("https://collinn.github.io/teaching/2023/data/target2.csv")
cohort2 <- read.csv("https://collinn.github.io/teaching/2023/data/cohort2.csv")

tc2 <- left_join(x = target2, y = cohort2, by = c("subjectID", "time"))

tc2long <- pivot_longer(tc2,
                        cols = !c(subjectID, time),
                        names_to = "Sound",
                        values_to = "Probability")

tc2sep <- separate(tc2long,
                   col = Sound,
                   into = c("Sound", "Type"),
                   sep = "\\.")

tc2sep$Type[tc2sep$Type == "x"] <- "Target"
tc2sep$Type[tc2sep$Type == "y"] <- "Cohort"

ggplot(tc2sep, aes(time, Probability)) +
  geom_line(aes(color = factor(subjectID))) + 
  geom_smooth(color = "Black") +
  facet_grid(Sound~Type) +
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position="none")
## `geom_smooth()` using method = 'gam' and formula = 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
